    tool_output=ToolOutput(
        output='# xAI Acquisition Details from the SpaceX S-1 Filing\n\nBased on my thorough review of all the provided filing excerpts, here is everything the S-1 discloses about the xAI acquisition, merger terms, and valuation:\n\n---\n\n## 1. Merger Structure & Timeline\n\n| Date | Event |\n|------|-------|\n| **October 2022** | Elon Musk acquires Twitter, Inc. |\n| **March 2023** | X.AI Corp. begins operations |\n| **March 28, 2025** | **X Merger** — xAI acquires X Holdings Corp. and X.AI Corp. (both become wholly-owned subsidiaries of xAI) |\n| **January 31, 2026** | Merger agreement signed (Exhibit 2.1) |\n| **February 2, 2026** | **xAI Merger** — SpaceX acquires X.AI Holdings Corp. (xAI becomes a wholly-owned subsidiary of SpaceX) |\n\nBoth mergers were effected through a **share exchange** and accounted for as **reorganizations of entities under common control**, because Elon Musk held a majority voting interest in SpaceX, xAI, and X throughout all periods presented.\n\n---\n\n## 2. xAI Merger Consideration\n\nThe specific consideration SpaceX paid in the xAI Merger (February 2, 2026):\n\n| Component | Amount |\n|-----------|--------|\n| Class A Common Stock issued | **321.7 million shares** (pre-2026 Stock Split) |\n| Class B Common Stock issued | **121.7 million shares** (pre-2026 Stock Split) |\n| Cash paid | **$2,947 million** |\n| **Total equity + cash** | **443.4 million shares + $2.95 billion cash** |\n\nThis was paid to holders of both xAI Common Stock and xAI Redeemable Convertible Preferred Stock.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Exchange Ratios\n\n### xAI → SpaceX\n- Each share of xAI Common Stock (Class A, Class B, or Limited Voting) converted at a **fixed exchange ratio of 0.1433 SpaceX shares** per xAI share (pre-2026 Stock Split basis)\n- **Cash election option**: Eligible service providers could elect to receive **$75.46 per share** of xAI Class A or Class B Common Stock instead of stock\n- xAI warrants were automatically exercised on a **cashless basis** and converted at the same 0.1433 ratio\n\n### X Holdings → xAI (preceding X Merger)\n- Each share of X Holdings Corp. Common Stock converted to **2.776 shares** of xAI Common Stock of the same class\n- Each share of X.AI Corp. Common Stock converted to **1.000 share** of xAI Common Stock\n- Each series of X.AI Corp. preferred stock (other than shares held by X) converted to **1.000 share** of xAI Redeemable Convertible Preferred Stock\n\n---\n\n## 4. Implied Valuation\n\nThe filing does **not** state an explicit private market valuation or purchase price allocation for xAI. However, we can derive an **implied per-share value** from the disclosure:\n\n- The **cash election price** was **$75.46 per xAI share**\n- The **stock exchange ratio** was **0.1433 SpaceX shares per xAI share**\n\nIf we use the cash election as a floor price, the total xAI consideration based on roughly 39 million shares that received cash (implied by the $2,947M cash payment ÷ $75.46) suggests the remaining ~3+ billion xAI-equivalent shares were converted into the 443.4 million SpaceX shares.\n\n**Critically**, because this was a **common-control transaction**, the S-1 explicitly states:\n\n> *"No new goodwill or other intangible assets have been recorded and all historical related party transactions between the entities have been eliminated in consolidation."*\n\n> *"The Company\'s consolidated financial statements have been prepared to reflect the retrospective combination of the net assets of the entities at their **historical carrying amounts** for all periods presented."*\n\nThis means there is **no traditional purchase price allocation** — the net assets of xAI and X are carried at their historical book values, not at fair market value.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Tesla\'s Investment in xAI → SpaceX Shares\n\n| Detail | Amount |\n|--------|--------|\n| Tesla agreed to invest in xAI (January 2026) | **$2,000 million** via xAI Series E Redeemable Convertible Preferred Stock |\n| After xAI Merger, this right converted into | SpaceX Class A Common Stock |\n| Shares issued to Tesla (March 12, 2026) | **3.8 million shares** (pre-2026 Stock Split basis) |\n\nThis implies Tesla\'s $2B investment converted at a rate that valued SpaceX shares at approximately **$526 per share** pre-split ($2,000M ÷ 3.8M shares), which could be used as an **indirect valuation benchmark** for xAI\'s Series E preferred.\n\n---\n\n## 6. xAI Pre-Merger Share Repurchase\n\nIn **2025**, SpaceX (prior to the merger) purchased **11.8 million shares of xAI Common Stock for $600 million** from an existing xAI shareholder — implying a price of approximately **$50.85 per xAI share**.\n\n---\n\n## 7. xAI Redeemable Convertible Preferred Stock (Pre-Merger Capital Structure)\n\n| Series | Shares Outstanding (millions) |\n|--------|-------------------------------|\n| Series A | 750.0 |\n| Series A-1 | — |\n| Series B | 584.9 |\n| Series C | 277.1 |\n| Series D | 120.1 |\n| Series E | 179.2 |\n| **Total** | **1,911.3** |\n\nThe table shows **$0 for all liquidation preferences and aggregate values** because, post-merger, these were converted into SpaceX equity and are now presented as part of the combined capital structure.\n\n---\n\n## 8. Musk\'s Performance Stock Award (Assumed from xAI)\n\nIn connection with the xAI Merger, SpaceX assumed a performance stock award originally granted by xAI on November 26, 2025:\n- Right to receive Class A shares equal to **0.20% of fully diluted capitalization** per milestone\n- **12 valuation milestones** from **$1.065 trillion to $6.565 trillion** (each $500B apart)\n- First milestone achieved pre-merger → Musk was issued **25,172,695 shares** of Class A common stock\n\n---\n\n## Summary: What\'s Missing\n\nThe S-1 **does not disclose**:\n- A standalone fair market valuation of xAI at the time of the merger\n- A purchase price allocation (because common-control accounting doesn\'t require one)\n- xAI\'s standalone revenue, EBITDA, or financial metrics pre-consolidation (though some related-party revenue figures are disclosed for xAI\'s agreements with Tesla)\n\nThe **strongest valuation signals** available from the filing are:\n1. The **$75.46/share cash election price** for xAI common stock\n2. The **$600M buyback of 11.8M xAI shares** (~$50.85/share) in 2025\n3. The **$2B Tesla Series E investment** converting to 3.8M SpaceX shares (~$526/share pre-split)\n4. The **total consideration** of 443.4M SpaceX shares + $2.95B cash',
